- It was Alice!
- Maybe they both sang.

1226
01:23:47,088 --> 01:23:50,285
- You don't know!
- We're gonna catch the Crossbow Killer.

1227
01:23:50,358 --> 01:23:52,292
He comes quietly,

1228
01:23:52,360 --> 01:23:55,761
or we blow him away.

1229
01:23:58,299 --> 01:24:00,199
No.

1230
01:24:01,069 --> 01:24:02,661
Mmm.

1231
01:24:02,737 --> 01:24:04,864
Some vigilantes.

1232
01:24:04,973 --> 01:24:07,407
Officially sanctioned
by the homeless.

1233
01:24:09,544 --> 01:24:11,239
I saw something.

1234
01:24:14,416 --> 01:24:16,213
What is that?

1235
01:24:17,519 --> 01:24:19,578
- It's the cops.
- Oh my God.

1236
01:24:19,654 --> 01:24:21,884
- Dirk, kiss Grace passionately.
- What?

1237
01:24:21,956 --> 01:24:24,015
I have a gun in my jacket.
We're vigilantes.

1238
01:24:24,092 --> 01:24:25,684
They'll think you're lovers.
Kiss her.

1239
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:27,352
- No.
- Then kiss me.

1240
01:24:27,429 --> 01:24:29,021
I'm not kissing anyone.

1241
01:24:42,844 --> 01:24:43,572
Did you see that?

1242
01:24:43,678 --> 01:24:46,112
What?

1243
01:24:48,583 --> 01:24:50,744
Did you ever see a movie called
''Don't Look Now''?

1244
01:25:10,371 --> 01:25:12,737
What are you
doing down here?

1245
01:25:12,841 --> 01:25:14,468
Um...

1246
01:25:15,944 --> 01:25:17,878
I was necking
with my boyfriend.

1247
01:25:17,946 --> 01:25:20,972
Dirk!

1248
01:25:21,082 --> 01:25:23,880
Good evening, officers.

1249
01:25:26,821 --> 01:25:29,153
You this young lady's boyfriend?

1250
01:25:34,195 --> 01:25:35,685
I am.

1251
01:25:37,732 --> 01:25:39,563
What are you doing?

1252
01:25:39,634 --> 01:25:41,261
I was watching them.

1253
01:25:41,336 --> 01:25:43,600
You know these people?

1254
01:25:43,671 --> 01:25:46,071
- Yes.
- No.

1255
01:25:47,208 --> 01:25:48,937
Oops.

1256
01:25:53,648 --> 01:25:56,811
Don't worry. Nothing terrible.
Carrying a concealed weapon.

1257
01:25:56,885 --> 01:26:00,286
And if you brought Pokey here
to shame me, it didn't work.

1258
01:26:00,355 --> 01:26:04,451
It was my first offense so they knocked it
down to a misdemeanor.

1259
01:26:04,526 --> 01:26:07,689
Oh, Mommy missed you.

1260
01:26:17,172 --> 01:26:18,935
What are you doing?

1261
01:26:24,779 --> 01:26:27,441
There's a court
appearance next week.

1262
01:26:27,515 --> 01:26:30,109
There'll be a significant fine to pay.

1263
01:26:31,920 --> 01:26:35,913
They didn't charge you,
Grace, or, um

1264
01:26:35,990 --> 01:26:37,287
Dirk.

1265
01:26:41,362 --> 01:26:43,353
That's Dirk?

1266
01:26:43,431 --> 01:26:45,365
Mm-hm.

1267
01:26:46,568 --> 01:26:48,160
Thank you
for coming, Max.

1268
01:26:48,236 --> 01:26:50,534
Oh, no.

1269
01:26:52,006 --> 01:26:54,634
We need to talk, Grace.

1270
01:26:54,742 --> 01:26:56,334
You sold our furniture.

1271
01:26:56,444 --> 01:26:59,845
Oh, no, no.
I was angry.

1272
01:26:59,914 --> 01:27:01,745
It's really
back in my place.

1273
01:27:01,816 --> 01:27:03,215
Oh.

1274
01:27:07,555 --> 01:27:11,616
Uh, look.
Why don't I take you to breakfast?

1275
01:27:25,573 --> 01:27:28,041
Well, you're
not dull anymore, Grace.

1276
01:27:31,346 --> 01:27:34,281
I was the one who wanted
to do dangerous things.

1277
01:27:34,349 --> 01:27:35,782
Look at you
in the last two weeks.

1278
01:27:35,883 --> 01:27:38,716
You've been to England.
Tracked a serial killer.

1279
01:27:38,786 --> 01:27:42,244
Been arrested.
Made new friends.

1280
01:27:44,459 --> 01:27:46,723
