is changed apartments.

1281
01:27:46,794 --> 01:27:50,025
I haven't even managed
to unpack my things.

1282
01:27:52,500 --> 01:27:54,468
I don't want a divorce.

1283
01:27:58,606 --> 01:28:01,541
Dirk,
Grace is my wife,

1284
01:28:01,643 --> 01:28:04,009
and I am going
to fight you for her.

1285
01:28:05,847 --> 01:28:08,645
I realize I've been
a complete fool.

1286
01:28:08,716 --> 01:28:13,153
And I guess what I'm asking is that
you give up Dirk here.

1287
01:28:13,221 --> 01:28:15,712
But Max, darling,
I'm afraid you're ow!

1288
01:28:19,861 --> 01:28:22,421
Yeah, but then again, Max.

1289
01:28:22,497 --> 01:28:25,398
Look here, Max...

1290
01:28:27,001 --> 01:28:29,231
Grace is my woman now.

1291
01:28:32,373 --> 01:28:35,137
Grace, I know he's young.
And handsome.

1292
01:28:35,243 --> 01:28:37,234
Oh, thanks.

1293
01:28:37,345 --> 01:28:40,542
But we've put in a lot
of years together, kid.

1294
01:28:40,615 --> 01:28:43,812
And when you've got
two people like us,

1295
01:28:43,885 --> 01:28:47,878
with all the good stuff behind us

1296
01:28:47,955 --> 01:28:50,583
and good stuff that could be,

1297
01:28:50,658 --> 01:28:55,721
it just doesn't make sense to discard it,
right? I mean, it

1298
01:28:59,167 --> 01:29:02,398
First time we met,
how cold it was.

1299
01:29:02,470 --> 01:29:05,462
You lent me your scarf.

1300
01:29:05,540 --> 01:29:10,000
And then that silly little apartment
in Milwaukee my first job.

1301
01:29:11,746 --> 01:29:16,649
How far would I travel
to be where you are?

1302
01:29:16,751 --> 01:29:20,619
What is the distance
from here to a star?

1303
01:29:20,688 --> 01:29:25,148
And if I ever lost you,
how much would I cry?

1304
01:29:25,226 --> 01:29:28,127
How deep is the ocean...

1305
01:29:36,904 --> 01:29:40,931
Ah... you don't
want to take me back.

1306
01:29:41,042 --> 01:29:43,101
It's over.

1307
01:29:47,415 --> 01:29:49,645
Max!

1308
01:29:50,985 --> 01:29:53,317
Max!

1309
01:30:02,430 --> 01:30:05,092
He needs me.

1310
01:30:08,202 --> 01:30:11,399
He fought for me.

1311
01:30:11,472 --> 01:30:14,032
Nobody's ever fought for me.

1312
01:30:20,548 --> 01:30:22,277
Here's the key
to my apartment.

1313
01:30:22,350 --> 01:30:26,480
It was staring us
in the face all the time.

1314
01:30:26,554 --> 01:30:28,545
What was?

1315
01:30:28,623 --> 01:30:31,990
The reason he chose Victor,
and the tramps.

1316
01:30:34,529 --> 01:30:37,623
There wasn't a reason.

1317
01:30:40,435 --> 01:30:43,097
I want you to stay
as long as you like.

1318
01:30:48,242 --> 01:30:51,609
Off you go.

1319
01:31:06,360 --> 01:31:09,124
I'm British
and I need a gun.

1320
01:31:09,864 --> 01:31:10,990
Oh!

1321
01:31:11,065 --> 01:31:14,398
It's...
Nice, Max.

1322
01:31:15,736 --> 01:31:19,729
It... It doesn't
feel like home.

1323
01:31:22,977 --> 01:31:24,535
Do you know
what I'd like to do?

1324
01:31:24,645 --> 01:31:27,079
- What's that?
- I'd like to sing.

1325
01:31:27,148 --> 01:31:29,742
- Why don't you?
- You mean it?

1326
01:31:29,817 --> 01:31:33,253
I missed your singing.
It always drove me crazy but...

1327
01:31:33,321 --> 01:31:35,448
when it wasn't there
I really missed it.

1328
01:31:35,523 --> 01:31:37,957
Oh, no. I don't mean
around the house.

1329
01:31:38,025 --> 01:31:40,550
I mean,
sing to people.

1330
01:31:42,063 --> 01:31:44,531
You mean in public?

1331
01:31:44,599 --> 01:31:47,227
Yeah. I'd be scared,
but yeah.

1332
01:31:47,301 --> 01:31:49,292
ln a bar.

1333
01:31:50,505 --> 01:31:53,167
You want to be
a lounge singer?

1334
01:31:53,274 --> 01:31:57,301
Well, at first.
And then, who knows?

1335
01:31:57,411 --> 01:32:00,471
I mean,
anything's possible.

1336
01:32:00,548 --> 01:32:03,108
Well, I agree
that anything's possible

1337
01:32:03,184 --> 01:32:05,311
but it's not
very realistic, is it?

1338
01:32:05,386 --> 01:32:08,480
I mean,
shouldn't you have...

1339
01:32:08,556 --> 01:32:12,219
explored this line
of work earlier...

1340
01:32:12,293 --> 01:32:14,818
when you were younger?

1341
01:32:14,896 --> 01:32:17,797
So that you might have
had the opportunity

1342
01:32:17,865 --> 01:32:21,733
and the time to
to fail?

1343
01:32:21,802 --> 01:32:24,930
But what about
dangerous things, Max?

1344
01:32:25,006 --> 01:32:28,942
Oh, I think we've done
our dangerous things.

1345
01:32:29,043 --> 01:32:32,501
I mean, I've had enough danger
to last a lifetime.

1346
01:32:34,448 --> 01:32:36,143
So...

1347
01:32:37,919 --> 01:32:39,682
you want it
the way it was?

1348
01:32:39,754 --> 01:32:44,157
No.
Similar, but different.

1349
01:34:07,875 --> 01:34:10,639
''Hello, you've reached
Andrew and Maudey.

1350
01:34:10,711 --> 01:34:12,611
That's right,
we're back together.

1351
01:34:12,680 --> 01:34:15,877
So for those of you who doubted that
this was a marriage made in heaven,

1352
01:34:15,950 --> 01:34:17,941
Fuck you!''

1353
01:34:18,019 --> 01:34:19,919
No, too bitter.

1354
01:34:20,955 --> 01:34:23,116
''Hello, I'm a goddess.

1355
01:34:23,190 --> 01:34:26,421
He got down on his knees
and begged me.''

1356
01:34:26,494 --> 01:34:29,190
Hello.

1357
01:34:29,263 --> 01:34:31,094
- Maudey?
- Grace?

1358
01:34:31,165 --> 01:34:33,827
Why do you think the Crossbow Killer
chose Victor?

1359
01:34:34,869 --> 01:34:37,599
Grace, remember closure?
Well, we closed.

1360
01:34:37,672 --> 01:34:40,368
But Dirk said
there was a reason.

1361
01:34:40,474 --> 01:34:42,499
He said it was staring us
in the face.

1362
01:34:42,610 --> 01:34:44,601
The reason is
he met a psycho.

1363
01:34:44,712 --> 01:34:47,010
It could have been anyone.

1364
01:34:47,081 --> 01:34:49,174
But it wasn't anyone.
It was Victor Fox.

1365
01:34:49,250 --> 01:34:52,549
- And two tramps.
- We got what we wanted.

1366
01:34:52,620 --> 01:34:55,145
I got Andrew,
you got Max.

1367
01:34:55,222 --> 01:34:58,089
We should be happy and getting on
with our new lives.

1368
01:34:58,159 --> 01:34:59,683
What about Dirk?

1369
01:34:59,760 --> 01:35:01,819
No matter what I do...

1370
01:35:01,896 --> 01:35:03,830
Go back to bed, Grace.

1371
01:35:03,898 --> 01:35:06,696
Whatever happened between you
and Dirk is over.

1372
01:35:06,767 --> 01:35:08,632
Doesn't matter where you go
or what you do

1373
01:35:08,703 --> 01:35:12,469
I want to spend each day
of my life with you...

1374
01:35:12,573 --> 01:35:16,634
You're right.
I got what I wanted.

1375
01:35:16,744 --> 01:35:18,939
Didn't I?

1376
01:35:19,013 --> 01:35:21,140
- Now listen, honey...
- It's singing.

1377
01:35:21,215 --> 01:35:24,082
- What?
- Remember what the tramp said?

1378
01:35:24,151 --> 01:35:26,176
The ones who were killed
were singing all the time.

1379
01:35:26,253 --> 01:35:30,212
- What if Victor was singing too?
- He kills anyone who sings.

1380
01:37:38,485 --> 01:37:41,010
Grace!

1381
01:37:41,088 --> 01:37:43,522
Grace!

1382
01:38:22,563 --> 01:38:24,793
What are you doing?

1383
01:38:26,867 --> 01:38:28,960
I'm trying to attract
the Crossbow Killer.

1384
01:38:29,036 --> 01:38:30,799
We thought you were
going to sing.

1385
01:38:30,871 --> 01:38:33,567
- Were did you get that gun?
- What are you wearing?

1386
01:38:33,674 --> 01:38:36,609
It's Victor's. He wore a suit like this
on the night he died.

1387
01:38:36,710 --> 01:38:38,769
Dirk, you're gonna
get yourself killed.

1388
01:38:38,879 --> 01:38:40,210
You know what Victor
used to say?

1389
01:38:40,281 --> 01:38:42,545
''A life lived in fear

1390
01:38:42,616 --> 01:38:44,709
isn't a life worth living.''

1391
01:38:46,287 --> 01:38:48,255
- No he didn't.
- What do you mean, ''No he didn't''?

1392
01:38:48,322 --> 01:38:52,258
He said, ''A life lived in fear...
isn't much fun.''

1393
01:38:52,326 --> 01:38:54,419
- ''lsn't much fun''?
- Yes, worth living but not much fun.

1394
01:38:54,495 --> 01:38:56,827
- Come off it. Victor would never say that.
- Can we get out of here?

1395
01:38:56,897 --> 01:39:00,355
I happen to know he did.
A bartender told me.

1396
01:39:00,434 --> 01:39:02,493
Does Max love you?

1397
01:39:04,171 --> 01:39:07,800
It's a simple question.
Did he tell you he loved you?

1398
01:39:09,777 --> 01:39:11,836
ln his way.

1399
01:39:11,946 --> 01:39:13,573
Good.

1400
01:39:13,647 --> 01:39:15,581
Now piss off.

1401
01:39:15,683 --> 01:39:20,313
Unlike the two of you,
I have fears to face.

1402
01:39:28,696 --> 01:39:31,688
- Dirk, you did it.
- Now what?

1403
01:39:31,765 --> 01:39:33,460
I don't know.
I didn't think it would work.

1404
01:39:33,534 --> 01:39:35,832
Don't move. Far as I know he can only
shoot one of us at a time.

1405
01:39:35,903 --> 01:39:37,734
- Which one?
- You're the one in the glitter suit.

1406
01:39:37,805 --> 01:39:38,999
Stay together.

1407
01:39:39,073 --> 01:39:40,904
Maybe you shouldn't stay
too close to Dirk, Grace.

1408
01:39:41,008 --> 01:39:42,703
God, I think I just got us all killed.

1409
01:39:42,810 --> 01:39:44,368
No!

1410
01:39:46,547 --> 01:39:48,606
You I know you.

1411
01:39:49,750 --> 01:39:51,149
Who?

1412
01:39:51,218 --> 01:39:53,118
You're her in the room
with the baby.

1413
01:39:53,187 --> 01:39:55,382
You mean Pokey?

1414
01:39:55,456 --> 01:39:57,890
You saw me
with my grandson?

1415
01:39:59,493 --> 01:40:01,324
Who are you?

1416
01:40:10,938 --> 01:40:13,202
I do know you.

1417
01:40:14,708 --> 01:40:16,699
You clean my windows.

1418
01:40:19,346 --> 01:40:22,281
Seeing you
and that baby dancing...

1419
01:40:24,084 --> 01:40:26,951
reminded me of my mother...

1420
01:40:27,021 --> 01:40:30,479
and her love.

1421
01:40:32,693 --> 01:40:35,321
For God's sake,
say something.

1422
01:40:35,396 --> 01:40:36,795
Yes

1423
01:40:36,864 --> 01:40:38,889
You're not gonna be loved
pointing a crossbow at people.

1424
01:40:38,966 --> 01:40:41,059
You!

1425
01:40:41,135 --> 01:40:44,070
- You're just like everybody else!
- No, we're not!

1426
01:40:44,138 --> 01:40:46,265
Look at us.
Do we look like everybody else?

1427
01:40:46,340 --> 01:40:48,308
We're not.
We're like you.

1428
01:40:48,409 --> 01:40:50,309
We're unloved, unnoticed.

1429
01:40:50,377 --> 01:40:52,368
I am not unnoticed.
Don't you read the papers?

1430
01:40:52,479 --> 01:40:54,845
Yes you're very famous.
Even I've heard of you, and I'm British.

1431
01:40:54,915 --> 01:40:56,109
I know that jacket.

1432
01:40:56,183 --> 01:40:58,014
No, you don't.
Everyone's wearing them in Britain

1433
01:40:58,085 --> 01:40:59,746
They're all the rage.
The streets are a-glitter.

1434
01:40:59,820 --> 01:41:02,550
What were you and the baby dancing to?
What was that song?

1435
01:41:05,893 --> 01:41:09,021
It was a song
by Victor Fox.

1436
01:41:10,364 --> 01:41:12,298
Oh.

1437
01:41:14,701 --> 01:41:17,033
I didn't mean
to hurt him.

1438
01:41:17,104 --> 01:41:20,130
My mother had a lot
of his records.

1439
01:41:21,642 --> 01:41:23,576
But he was walking alone
and he was singing

1440
01:41:23,644 --> 01:41:26,772
and when they sing it makes me think of
my mother and I get sad.

1441
01:41:26,847 --> 01:41:29,645
I have to make
them stop.

1442
01:41:34,755 --> 01:41:37,246
What was that song
you were singing to the baby?

1443
01:41:37,324 --> 01:41:39,349
What?

1444
01:41:41,562 --> 01:41:42,790
Was it...

1445
01:41:42,863 --> 01:41:44,922
Was it
''I Can't Smile Without You''?

1446
01:41:44,998 --> 01:41:47,660
My mother used to sing that to me
when I was little.

1447
01:41:47,734 --> 01:41:49,361
- No...
- Yes, it was.

1448
01:41:49,436 --> 01:41:51,904
Yes, it was.

1449
01:41:51,972 --> 01:41:53,405
Yes, it was.

1450
01:41:59,480 --> 01:42:00,845
How does that go again?

1451
01:42:00,914 --> 01:42:02,677
Huh?

1452
01:42:02,749 --> 01:42:04,740
All right,
sing it for me!

1453
01:42:19,099 --> 01:42:21,932
<i>You know I...</i>

1454
01:42:22,002 --> 01:42:27,941
<i>Can't smile without you</i>

1455
01:42:28,041 --> 01:42:33,479
<i>I can't smile without you</i>

1456
01:42:33,580 --> 01:42:39,143
<i>I can't laugh and I can't sing</i>

1457
01:42:39,219 --> 01:42:45,454
<i>I'm finding it hard to do anything</i>

1458
01:42:45,526 --> 01:42:49,792
<i>You see, I feel sad</i>

1459
01:42:49,863 --> 01:42:53,162
<i>When you're sad</i>

1460
01:43:08,382 --> 01:43:12,910
<i>Feel glad when you're glad</i>

